In Germany, taxable persons have to file their previous applications at the latest 10 days after the end of the calendar quarter or the calendar month, depending on the amount of their tax liability in the previous year.
The annual VAT declaration must be submitted no later than 31 May of the following year.
The obligation to issue an annual VAT return has some advantages and disadvantages:
+ At the end of the calendar year, the taxpayer can correct the errors in the monthly pre-registrations by filing a single VAT return;
