In order to avoid bureaucracy, the levying of the ZM could be linked to the filing of VAT returns or pre-notifications.
However, an obligation to provide ZM on a monthly basis would cause more periodic discrepancies between the information on intra-Community supplies and those on intra-Community purchases and increase the flow of data between CLOs.
In 2006, the Federal Government considered the general introduction of monthly ZMs.
The implementation failed due to the concerns of the federal states.
They feared that a monthly transmission of VIES data to the CLO of other Member States could lead to misunderstandings and confusion.
In order for the obligation to provide ZM on a monthly basis to be effective, it is necessary to agree on the uniform monthly fee at European level, so that a monthly update of the VIES data is possible.
